# Deployment and Operations

## Docker

- Main app image: app/Dockerfile
  - Multi-stage: deps → build (pnpm prisma generate + nuxt build) → runner
  - Runtime runs .output/server/index.mjs; includes prisma/ for field-encryption docs
- Microservice image: microservice/Dockerfile
  - Multi-stage with prisma generate during build
  - Final runner uses pnpm start; supports NODE_ENV=test to run test-start
  - Target runner-keyrotate adds kubectl/jq for CronJob container

## Kubernetes manifests

- .deploy/dineros.template.yaml
  - Two Deployments: main app and microservice
  - Services for app and microservice; Ingress for app
  - Environment via Secrets (DATABASE_URL in separate secret refs; DB encryption keys grouped in SECRET_DB)
  - Redis host/port injected (cluster service names)
  - Readiness/liveness/startup probes on http endpoints (/health/ready, /health/live)
- Staging-only manifests
  - .deploy/key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml — nightly DB field-encryption key rotation + microservice migrate call
  - .deploy/key-rotation-rbac.template.yaml — Role/RoleBinding for rotating the SECRET_DB and patching Deployments

Render manifests with envsubst using .deploy/profiles/<profile>.env and environment variables (GCP_PROJECT_ID, IMAGE_TAG, etc.).

## CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

- .github/workflows/main.yml
  - On push to main/master: build app and microservice (push to gcr.io), then deploy to production GKE
- .github/workflows/pr.yml
  - PR checks: lint, tests, pre-commit security (TruffleHog), CodeQL
  - If PR branch is in same repo: build images with tag pr-<N>-<SHA>, deploy to staging, verify rollout and health
  - Posts optional Cursor Bugbot trigger comment
- .github/actions/build-push-gcr/
  - Composite action: authenticates to gcloud, configures Docker, and uses buildx to push tagged images
- .github/actions/deploy-dineros-gke/
  - Renders templates and applies with kubectl; staging applies key-rotation resources

## Environments and configuration

- app/server/envSchema.ts + env.ts define/parse required variables
- .env.example lists expected variables (DB, Redis, Plaid, Postmark, JWT, etc.)
- For Prisma codegen during Docker build, a placeholder DATABASE_URL is used; runtime sets actual via env/secret

## Health endpoints

- /health/ready — readiness probe
- /health/live — liveness probe

## Local development

- docker-compose.yaml brings up MySQL 8.0.43 and Redis 8.4.0 locally (ports 3309, 6380)
- Follow README for pnpm install, prisma migrate deploy, pnpm dev
- In cloud CI agents (e.g., Cursor), see AGENTS.md for MySQL/Redis startup notes and DATABASE_URL override

